> We love good Cheesy Chorizo Chipotle Bean Quesadillas with Avocado & Salad and this deliciously simple, chef-curated recipe doesn't disappoint. Time to bust out the pots and pans!

== Bean Mixture ==

Drain and rinse the @mixed beans{1%can}.

Pop into a #bowl{} and roughly mash with the back of a #fork{} or a #potato masher{}.

Trim the @spring onions{2} then slice thinly.

Grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{60%g}.

Add the spring onion, cheese, @chipotle paste{20%g} and @tomato puree{30%g} to the beans.

Season with @salt{}, @ground black pepper{} and a @sugar{pinch}. Mix well.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on high heat. Add the @chorizo{90%g} to the pan, stir fry until starting to crisp for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once cooked remove the chorizo and stir into the bean mixture.

> MOD: If you've added chorizo to your meal, once you've made the beans, heat a drizzle of oil in a frying pan on high heat. Add the chorizo to the pan and stir fry for 2-3 mins. Once cooked remove the chorizo and stir into the bean mixture.

== Quesadillas ==

Lay the @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{4} out on a #board{}.

Spread a little of the bean mix over half of each, leaving a small border round the edge, then fold the tortillas in half to make half moon shapes.

Wash out the frying pan used for the chorizo, pop back on the heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

> MOD: If you've added chorizo to your meal, wash out the frying pan used for the chorizo and pop back onto the heat, follow the remaining step above.

When hot, carefully lay the quesadillas in the pan. Fry until golden, ~{2%minutes} each side. Turn carefully.

Lightly press down on the tortillas with a #spatula{} to ensure they stick together and brown nicely.

> TIP: You may have to do this in batches, adding a little more oil to the pan each time - just cover the cooked quesadillas with foil to keep warm.

== Avocado, Tomato and Rocket Salad ==

While the quesadillas are frying, slice lengthways into the @avocado{1}. Once you reach the stone turn the avocado around to cut it in half. Twist each half and pull it apart. Remove the stone then scoop out the insides onto a board. Roughly chop the avocado.

Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125}.

In a #large bowl{}, combine the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml} with the @olive oil{1%tbsp}.

Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Add the @wild rocket{40%g}, tomatoes and avocado and toss gently.

== To Serve ==

Serve the quesadillas alongside plenty of rocket salad. Enjoy!